        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4447344880" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17587363516205167079">The Jeanette is my absolute favorite of what I call my &quot;arctic, armchair exploration&quot; books. It&apos;s the most harrowing thing that I&apos;ve ever read. <br/>This book by Mr. Sides isn&apos;t my favorite of these, but it&apos;s definitely second! It&apos;s still a messed the hell up tale! <br/>I would have been one of the crazy people to set sail or steam to see the North. The Northwest passage? Sign me up. <br/>I have an app that I fall asleep to, and it&apos;s the sound of ice, breaking off of a wooden ship. I love it. <br/>Would I have been</span>
  <span id="freeText17587363516205167079" style="display:none">The Jeanette is my absolute favorite of what I call my "arctic, armchair exploration" books. It's the most harrowing thing that I've ever read. <br />This book by Mr. Sides isn't my favorite of these, but it's definitely second! It's still a messed the hell up tale! <br />I would have been one of the crazy people to set sail or steam to see the North. The Northwest passage? Sign me up. <br />I have an app that I fall asleep to, and it's the sound of ice, breaking off of a wooden ship. I love it. <br />Would I have been so brave after my ship was crushed by ice, and I had to take to land? <br />I think not! But, I often surprise myself with how stubbornly brave I can be.<br />Eh! I hate the heat. Good thing I live in Montana! <br />-17 now, and the snow is beautiful!</span>
